node.title: Tumbling Waters
node.description: Amicalola Creek in Dawsonville, GA.  Amicalola is derived from a Cherokee word meaning "tumbling waters."

node.title: In Your Face
node.description:
Another from the Raptor Show....
A Barred Owl.

node.title: In the Middle
node.description: Somewhere around the middle of Amicalola Falls is a bridge where you can view the upper part of the falls.  This is a great place to enjoy the scene, but a difficult place to get a photograph with all the spray coming off the falls.

node.title: Hawk Stare
node.description: We were unexpectedly treated to a raptor show during our trip to Amicalola Falls.  The stars of the show are their owls, but this red tailed hawk made quite the imression as well.

node.description: Cascade Run along the creek trail at Amicalola Falls State Park.
